                            <comment id="12895671" author="fmeschbe" created="Thu, 5 Aug 2010 13:22:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in Rev. 982605. Support separation between &quot;no method to be called&quot; and &quot;method execution failure&quot; situations to handle according specification:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;activate method failure is logged and must cause activation failure&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;deactivate method failure is just logged&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;modified method failure is just logged&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;bind method failure is just logged&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;unbind method failure is just logged&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Callers of the BaseMethod.invoke method now indicates, whether a failure executing the method should be an invocation failure or just be logged but then assumed to be ok.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12898889" author="fmeschbe" created="Mon, 16 Aug 2010 12:11:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Apache Felix Declarative Services 1.6.0 has been released. The issues are now closed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
